WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.140 --> 00:00:07.540
He was born
the youngest of nine.

2
00:00:07.670 --> 00:00:09.910
Hard to imagine now.

3
00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:13.380
but our gentle giant
of a K-9 agent. Gary Callahan.

4
00:00:13.510 --> 00:00:14.980
was the runt of his litter.

5
00:00:15.710 --> 00:00:18.180
And that was the least
of his problems.

6
00:00:18.280 --> 00:00:20.220
His hind legs
were underdeveloped.

7
00:00:20.350 --> 00:00:23.720
Too weak to walk. he'd just
sit there. day after day.

8
00:00:23.820 --> 00:00:27.060
watching as his brothers
and sisters played.

9
00:00:30.190 --> 00:00:32.960
Then he watched
as they disappeared.

10
00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:36.070
One by one.

11
00:00:36.170 --> 00:00:38.330
they were all taken away.

12
00:00:38.400 --> 00:00:40.070
off to live
with their new families

13
00:00:40.200 --> 00:00:42.770
in their new homes.

14
00:00:43.670 --> 00:00:45.740
Until Gary was all alone.

15
00:00:46.510 --> 00:00:48.110
But he never gave up hope.

16
00:00:48.210 --> 00:00:51.150
He was sure that his time
would come. too.

17
00:00:51.210 --> 00:00:54.720
And then. one day.
it finally did.

18
00:00:54.820 --> 00:00:57.750
Bob Barker reminding you to
help control the pet population.

19
00:00:57.850 --> 00:00:59.890
Have your pets spayed
or neutered. Goodbye. everybody.

20
00:00:59.990 --> 00:01:03.430
Every great agent
has God-given instincts.

21
00:01:03.530 --> 00:01:05.590
and Gary's must have kicked in.

22
00:01:05.690 --> 00:01:07.130
His gut must have told him

23
00:01:07.230 --> 00:01:09.430
this wasn't going
to be his new home.

24
00:01:09.570 --> 00:01:12.240
And his gut was right.

25
00:01:13.670 --> 00:01:15.140
Now. maybe it was grit...

26
00:01:15.240 --> 00:01:18.070
or. hell.
maybe it was half a miracle...

27
00:01:18.170 --> 00:01:20.110
but without a moment to spare.

28
00:01:20.210 --> 00:01:23.280
Gary Callahan rose to all fours

29
00:01:23.380 --> 00:01:25.110
and took his first steps.

30
00:01:36.390 --> 00:01:38.960
But the new life he walked into

31
00:01:39.060 --> 00:01:41.460
wasn't going to be an easy one.

32
00:01:42.270 --> 00:01:45.130
He was scared. and all alone.

33
00:01:47.340 --> 00:01:50.140
And he lived that way
for a year...

34
00:01:52.070 --> 00:01:54.880
trying to survive in a world
that didn't seem to want him.

35
00:01:54.980 --> 00:01:56.380
Son of a bitch.

36
00:01:56.450 --> 00:01:57.710
How many times I got to tell you

37
00:01:57.780 --> 00:01:59.220
to get the hell out of here?

38
00:02:00.550 --> 00:02:03.220
All Gary needed was someone
to give a damn.

39
00:02:03.320 --> 00:02:04.690
A helping hand.

40
00:02:04.790 --> 00:02:07.460
But all he ever got
was a boot to the neck.

41
00:02:08.190 --> 00:02:11.890
He outgrew his box.
but he couldn't let it go.

42
00:02:11.990 --> 00:02:14.430
It was the closest thing
to a home he ever had.

43
00:02:14.530 --> 00:02:16.330
Mom. look. Can I pet him?

44
00:02:16.470 --> 00:02:17.700
No. sweetie. no. not that one.

45
00:02:17.800 --> 00:02:19.740
Okay? Pet Lucy.

46
00:02:19.840 --> 00:02:21.500
Must have stung like hell

47
00:02:21.600 --> 00:02:23.510
to feel that unwanted.

48
00:02:23.640 --> 00:02:25.870
Like an outcast.

49
00:02:28.980 --> 00:02:31.910
German shepherds
are natural-born protectors.

50
00:02:32.010 --> 00:02:33.350
but even protectors

51
00:02:33.450 --> 00:02:35.450
need someone
looking out for them.

52
00:02:46.300 --> 00:02:49.530
Yeah. I called two hours ago.

53
00:02:49.670 --> 00:02:51.030
What took you so long?

54
00:02:51.130 --> 00:02:53.940
Hello?
Mr. Animal Control?

55
00:02:54.040 --> 00:02:56.510
I asked you a question.

56
00:02:57.270 --> 00:02:59.040
I heard you.
I just ain't answering

57
00:02:59.170 --> 00:03:00.840
'cause I don't like your tone.

58
00:03:01.840 --> 00:03:03.780
Now. where's the dog?

59
00:03:10.120 --> 00:03:12.560
Don't be scared. buddy.

60
00:03:13.690 --> 00:03:15.460
My name's Michael.

61
00:03:15.520 --> 00:03:17.460
and I promise you.
I ain't here to hurt you.

62
00:03:17.530 --> 00:03:20.260
How about I make you a deal?

63
00:03:21.130 --> 00:03:22.670
I'll get you a steak...

64
00:03:23.670 --> 00:03:26.600
if you just let me scoot you
out of here on your box.

65
00:03:27.440 --> 00:03:28.700
Okay. pal?

66
00:03:29.470 --> 00:03:31.140
Easy does it.

67
00:03:31.240 --> 00:03:34.910
Okay. we're gonna do this
nice and easy.

68
00:03:36.850 --> 00:03:38.650
You're such a good...
Aah!

69
00:04:02.740 --> 00:04:04.670
Gail. it's me. Where to?

70
00:04:04.770 --> 00:04:06.240
Okay. got it.

71
00:04:06.340 --> 00:04:08.240
Yeah. he's here.

72
00:04:09.080 --> 00:04:10.180
Gear up. Gare bear.

73
00:04:13.550 --> 00:04:14.950
Okay. on our way.

74
00:04:15.080 --> 00:04:16.790
Even the greatest protectors.

75
00:04:16.920 --> 00:04:18.850
like Gary Callahan.

76
00:04:18.950 --> 00:04:20.760
need protecting. too.

77
00:04:20.860 --> 00:04:22.830
A helping hand.

78
00:04:22.930 --> 00:04:24.990
-And on this night.
-Stay there.

79
00:04:25.090 --> 00:04:28.300
Gary would need it
more than ever.

80
00:04:45.280 --> 00:04:47.050
Evening. boss.
Well. it's 2:00 a.m..

81
00:04:47.150 --> 00:04:49.520
so I guess. technically.
I should be saying good morning.

82
00:04:49.620 --> 00:04:51.150
I never know what to do
in these situations.

83
00:04:51.250 --> 00:04:53.060
I just never know. do I. buddy?

84
00:04:53.150 --> 00:04:54.590
- Case. Rando.
- Uh...

85
00:04:54.660 --> 00:04:56.660
grocery store was broken into
a couple hours ago.

86
00:04:56.790 --> 00:04:59.900
The owner. Javier Martinez. 74.
was stabbed and killed.

87
00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:02.530
- Why ain't they handling it?
- Victim donated groceries

88
00:05:02.630 --> 00:05:04.370
to the Camp Pendleton
food pantry.

89
00:05:04.470 --> 00:05:06.130
When the cops found his
base ID card. they called us.

90
00:05:06.230 --> 00:05:08.840
Good thing. too. 'cause
they don't have a K-9 unit.

91
00:05:08.940 --> 00:05:10.440
We got a blood trail out back.

92
00:05:10.540 --> 00:05:12.240
We got a blood trail.
don't we. buddy?

93
00:05:12.340 --> 00:05:13.680
Stop doing that.

94
00:05:13.810 --> 00:05:15.580
- What else?
- Junior's finally getting baptized.

95
00:05:15.680 --> 00:05:17.310
which means I need
to pick a godfather.

96
00:05:17.410 --> 00:05:19.110
So. you're all being evaluated.

97
00:05:19.180 --> 00:05:20.420
Okay.

98
00:05:20.520 --> 00:05:22.180
Gary. halt.

99
00:05:23.020 --> 00:05:26.360
- Robber snagged his shirt.
- Yeah. seems that way.

100
00:05:26.460 --> 00:05:28.660
Oh. watch your back. boss.
Whole place was just painted.

101
00:05:32.230 --> 00:05:33.860
It seems to me like anytime

102
00:05:33.960 --> 00:05:36.200
there's a call
at the ass crack of dawn.

103
00:05:36.330 --> 00:05:37.430
it's Tango's night off.

104
00:05:37.500 --> 00:05:39.030
What do you think about that?

105
00:05:39.170 --> 00:05:41.040
Haven't given it much thought.

106
00:05:41.140 --> 00:05:43.140
Got defensive wounds here.

107
00:05:43.210 --> 00:05:46.010
Looks like he put up
a hell of a fight.

108
00:05:46.110 --> 00:05:47.940
Was he strangled and stabbed?

109
00:05:48.040 --> 00:05:49.980
Yeah. and I think
at the same time.

110
00:05:50.080 --> 00:05:51.580
- So. there was two of them?
- Yeah. boss.

111
00:05:51.680 --> 00:05:53.520
We're thinking robbery gone bad.

112
00:05:53.620 --> 00:05:56.520
Register was pried open.
emptied out.

113
00:05:56.650 --> 00:05:58.690
and then the killers
took off out the back.

114
00:05:58.820 --> 00:06:00.660
- One of them left a trail.
- I know.

115
00:06:00.760 --> 00:06:02.460
Gail said.
That's why I brought Gary.

116
00:06:02.560 --> 00:06:03.630
Where's Herm?

117
00:06:03.690 --> 00:06:05.030
He's his handler.
he should be here.

118
00:06:05.130 --> 00:06:06.930
I'll radio him.
see if he's close.

119
00:06:07.030 --> 00:06:08.330
I got some kind of

120
00:06:08.430 --> 00:06:10.200
sticky substance here

121
00:06:10.300 --> 00:06:13.870
next to this watch-shaped
tan line.

122
00:06:13.970 --> 00:06:16.040
Now. I am
no investigative genius

123
00:06:16.140 --> 00:06:19.510
like y'all fine folks.
but if I had to guess.

124
00:06:19.580 --> 00:06:21.710
I would say the killers
stole his watch.

125
00:06:21.810 --> 00:06:25.410
and one of them had
something sticky on their hand.

126
00:06:25.550 --> 00:06:27.520
So. he busts in through the
front and leaves out the back.

127
00:06:27.620 --> 00:06:28.920
They tripped the silent alarm.

128
00:06:29.050 --> 00:06:30.390
Probably heard the sirens
and took off

129
00:06:30.490 --> 00:06:31.820
- into the woods back there.
- The woods. huh?

130
00:06:31.890 --> 00:06:34.690
Sounds like a good place
to dump a murder weapon.

131
00:06:34.790 --> 00:06:36.260
Bad news. Herm's still at home.

132
00:06:36.360 --> 00:06:37.460
He said no one ever called him.

133
00:06:37.560 --> 00:06:39.060
Damn Gail.

134
00:06:39.160 --> 00:06:40.400
Yeah. he's throwing on clothes.
rushing out the door.

135
00:06:40.530 --> 00:06:41.560
but said he's at least
an hour out.

136
00:06:41.660 --> 00:06:42.830
Well. rain's coming.

137
00:06:42.930 --> 00:06:44.230
If the knife's out there.

138
00:06:44.330 --> 00:06:46.200
any prints and blood
will get washed away.

139
00:06:46.270 --> 00:06:48.400
Can't wait around
'cause Gail's an idiot.

140
00:06:48.500 --> 00:06:50.010
Showtime. bud.

141
00:06:50.110 --> 00:06:52.240
Get a good whiff.

142
00:06:53.010 --> 00:06:55.910
He's still got the best sniffer
this side of the Mississippi.

143
00:06:56.010 --> 00:06:58.450
Probie. with us.

144
00:07:25.540 --> 00:07:27.280
What is it. boy?

145
00:07:36.790 --> 00:07:38.620
Boss.

146
00:07:38.750 --> 00:07:39.960
You seeing this?

147
00:07:40.060 --> 00:07:41.660
Am I seeing what. probie?

148
00:07:41.760 --> 00:07:43.290
Stop!

149
00:07:43.430 --> 00:07:45.060
- Federal agents!
- Halt!

150
00:07:45.130 --> 00:07:46.530
Gary!

151
00:07:48.030 --> 00:07:50.400
- Stop!
- Damn it. Gary!

152
00:07:50.470 --> 00:07:52.000
Gary!

153
00:07:52.100 --> 00:07:55.000
Halt!
Damn it. Gary. halt!

154
00:07:58.810 --> 00:07:59.910
Gary!

155
00:07:59.980 --> 00:08:01.640
Go! Go!

156
00:08:05.250 --> 00:08:07.420
Aw. geez.
Boss.

157
00:08:08.850 --> 00:08:10.320
Go.

158
00:08:12.450 --> 00:08:14.590
No. no. no. no. no.

159
00:08:15.260 --> 00:08:17.830
Oh. no. no. no. no.
no. no. buddy.

160
00:08:18.660 --> 00:08:20.500
You're good. pal.

161
00:08:20.600 --> 00:08:22.330
He's been stabbed.

162
00:08:22.430 --> 00:08:24.670
Stay there. Gare.

163
00:08:26.740 --> 00:08:27.900
Agent down!

164
00:08:33.110 --> 00:08:34.780
Doc? Doc. you in there?

165
00:08:34.880 --> 00:08:36.780
Hey. doc. come on!

166
00:08:36.880 --> 00:08:39.010
- Thank you.
- He's lost a lot of blood. Chief.

167
00:08:39.080 --> 00:08:40.520
Get him on the table.

168
00:08:40.620 --> 00:08:43.120
- Hang in there. Gare bear.
- How many stab wounds?

169
00:08:43.220 --> 00:08:44.550
One. but it's bad.

170
00:08:44.650 --> 00:08:45.590
Dr. Friedman and I
packed the wound

171
00:08:45.720 --> 00:08:46.990
as well as we could.

172
00:08:47.060 --> 00:08:48.620
but we couldn't get
the bleeding to stop.

173
00:08:48.720 --> 00:08:50.330
There ain't no 24-hour vets
in the whole damn county.

174
00:08:50.430 --> 00:08:51.960
- I didn't know who else to call.
- It's okay.

175
00:08:52.060 --> 00:08:53.730
I'm glad you did.

176
00:08:54.600 --> 00:08:56.600
Uh. tell Rando...

177
00:08:57.270 --> 00:08:59.800
Tell Rando and Dominguez
to call all the hospitals.

178
00:08:59.900 --> 00:09:01.440
You heard that guy scream.

179
00:09:02.440 --> 00:09:04.410
Gare bit that bastard
pretty bad before...

180
00:09:04.510 --> 00:09:06.270
b-before he...

181
00:09:06.410 --> 00:09:08.010
We are on it. boss.

182
00:09:08.110 --> 00:09:11.010
No way we are not gonna find
the guy who did this.

183
00:09:11.110 --> 00:09:12.450
You got my word.

184
00:09:20.760 --> 00:09:23.090
You're a good boy.
you know that?

185
00:09:25.330 --> 00:09:27.630
You're such a good boy.

186
00:09:27.760 --> 00:09:30.130
He's the Antichrist.

187
00:09:30.970 --> 00:09:33.040
Yeah. this ain't good.

188
00:09:34.600 --> 00:09:36.240
We posted his picture
all over town.

189
00:09:36.340 --> 00:09:38.110
Why hasn't anyone called?

190
00:09:38.210 --> 00:09:41.540
He's a German shepherd.
He must belong to someone.

191
00:09:41.610 --> 00:09:43.180
Uh-huh.

192
00:09:44.580 --> 00:09:47.150
Mike?
You know something?

193
00:09:48.480 --> 00:09:51.220
Friend of mine at the pound
said. past couple years.

194
00:09:51.290 --> 00:09:53.320
a few baby Germans
got dumped on them

195
00:09:53.460 --> 00:09:55.220
with a genetic defect.

196
00:09:55.320 --> 00:09:58.290
They couldn't walk.
and all had to be put down.

197
00:09:59.700 --> 00:10:00.930
What's that have to do with him?

198
00:10:01.030 --> 00:10:02.330
They set up a security camera

199
00:10:02.430 --> 00:10:04.470
to catch the breeder
dumping them.

200
00:10:04.570 --> 00:10:07.440
One of the puppies
got up and walked away.

201
00:10:07.540 --> 00:10:09.140
I saw the video. Tish.

202
00:10:09.270 --> 00:10:10.710
Looked just like this one.

203
00:10:10.810 --> 00:10:12.570
And get this...

204
00:10:13.410 --> 00:10:15.140
he walked away with a box.

205
00:10:19.920 --> 00:10:21.950
I think he might be
the miracle dog.

206
00:10:22.020 --> 00:10:23.720
If he was dumped. Mike.

207
00:10:23.820 --> 00:10:25.190
that means no one's
looking for him

208
00:10:25.290 --> 00:10:26.720
because he doesn't have a home.

209
00:10:26.820 --> 00:10:28.520
So. I got to find him one.

210
00:10:29.860 --> 00:10:31.390
What?

211
00:10:31.490 --> 00:10:34.130
We both know that dog's
not going anywhere.

212
00:10:34.200 --> 00:10:35.860
No one's gonna take him.

213
00:10:35.960 --> 00:10:37.870
And you love him already anyway.

214
00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:40.100
Oh. I ain't got
any kind of feelings for him.

215
00:10:40.170 --> 00:10:41.970
Hell...

216
00:10:42.740 --> 00:10:44.170
I ain't even given him
a name yet.

217
00:10:44.310 --> 00:10:45.510
Oh. my God.

218
00:10:45.640 --> 00:10:47.210
Gary?

219
00:10:49.380 --> 00:10:50.650
Doc.

220
00:10:50.710 --> 00:10:52.450
He's sedated.

221
00:10:52.510 --> 00:10:55.020
We need to get him to a vet
for more surgery.

222
00:10:55.150 --> 00:10:56.950
But he's gonna be okay?

223
00:10:57.020 --> 00:10:59.350
We need to get him to a vet.

224
00:10:59.450 --> 00:11:01.220
The game warden's
been making calls.

225
00:11:01.320 --> 00:11:03.130
trying to get one to open early.

226
00:11:05.160 --> 00:11:07.430
- Maybe that's him now.
- I got it.

227
00:11:08.930 --> 00:11:10.570
- Hello.
- He's a tough boy. Herm.

228
00:11:10.700 --> 00:11:12.400
He'll pull through.

229
00:11:13.300 --> 00:11:14.570
How'd this happen?

230
00:11:15.400 --> 00:11:17.810
He spotted the killer.
took off after him. He's...

231
00:11:18.640 --> 00:11:20.210
He's a hero.

232
00:11:21.180 --> 00:11:22.810
Why wasn't he on his leash?

233
00:11:22.880 --> 00:11:24.510
'Cause you had it.

234
00:11:25.210 --> 00:11:27.120
Thought you were gonna be there.

235
00:11:28.950 --> 00:11:31.250
I-I can't lose him. man.

236
00:11:34.360 --> 00:11:35.520
We ain't gonna.

237
00:11:35.620 --> 00:11:37.490
Okay. thanks.

238
00:11:37.590 --> 00:11:39.190
That was Lala.

239
00:11:39.260 --> 00:11:41.660
They think they tracked down
the guy who did this.

240
00:11:41.730 --> 00:11:43.200
Where?

241
00:11:51.140 --> 00:11:52.810
- Who is he?
- Name's Adam Plum.

242
00:11:52.910 --> 00:11:55.380
Got caught robbing that
same grocery store last month.

243
00:11:55.440 --> 00:11:57.150
but the owner refused
to press charges.

244
00:11:57.250 --> 00:11:59.510
Plum's been living on the
streets. so he felt bad for him.

245
00:11:59.580 --> 00:12:01.180
Here's his mug shot.

246
00:12:01.280 --> 00:12:02.250
Red hoodie.

247
00:12:02.380 --> 00:12:03.890
I scouted the encampment.

248
00:12:03.950 --> 00:12:05.390
There's a tent down there

249
00:12:05.450 --> 00:12:07.020
with some bloody towels
outside of it.

250
00:12:07.120 --> 00:12:09.420
- You said Gary bit him. right?
- Hell yeah. he did.

251
00:12:09.560 --> 00:12:11.230
On me.

252
00:12:11.330 --> 00:12:12.930
Everyone out.
Federal agents.

253
00:12:13.030 --> 00:12:14.760
We're gonna need
to see some hands.

254
00:12:14.860 --> 00:12:17.300
Let's go. Give me your hands.
- Hands up. Hands up.

255
00:12:17.430 --> 00:12:19.800
Please. orderly form a line
right here. Come on.

256
00:12:19.900 --> 00:12:22.270
Okay. let's go.
Everybody out of the tents.

257
00:12:22.370 --> 00:12:24.470
- Over here. we're gonna...
- Over here. can you guys

258
00:12:24.610 --> 00:12:26.010
- please come over here. we need to see your hands.
- Drop everything.

259
00:12:26.110 --> 00:12:27.710
You don't a thing from inside.

260
00:12:27.780 --> 00:12:30.310
Let's go. Gather over here
in the open area.

261
00:12:36.680 --> 00:12:38.120
There. stay with him.

262
00:12:38.220 --> 00:12:39.190
Hey!

263
00:12:42.320 --> 00:12:43.560
Wait a minute!

264
00:12:48.630 --> 00:12:51.230
Get off me!
Get off me!

265
00:12:55.070 --> 00:12:56.840
Boss.

266
00:12:58.510 --> 00:13:01.510
Son of a bitch!

267
00:13:14.390 --> 00:13:17.090
Get him printed. then put
his ass down in the box.

268
00:13:17.230 --> 00:13:19.290
I'll see you soon. boy.

269
00:13:19.390 --> 00:13:20.600
Give him hell. Mike.

270
00:13:20.700 --> 00:13:23.100
Yeah. give that prick-hole hell.

271
00:13:25.100 --> 00:13:27.070
Franks. that was Herm.

272
00:13:27.200 --> 00:13:30.640
He said they just took Gary
into surgery.

273
00:13:30.740 --> 00:13:32.110
I thought they were
waiting for some

274
00:13:32.240 --> 00:13:33.540
- fancy specialist or something.
- They wanted to.

275
00:13:33.640 --> 00:13:35.080
but Gary's blood pressure
suddenly dropped.

276
00:13:35.180 --> 00:13:36.580
so they couldn't wait
any longer.

277
00:13:36.680 --> 00:13:38.580
Then who's doing the surgery?
Some half-wit?

278
00:13:39.450 --> 00:13:40.920
I'm heading to the vet.
Tell Rando

279
00:13:41.020 --> 00:13:43.590
- to do the interrogation.
- Franks. your shirt.

280
00:13:43.690 --> 00:13:46.790
I put a fresh one
in your locker.

281
00:13:46.920 --> 00:13:48.290
Thank you. Mary Jo.

282
00:13:52.130 --> 00:13:53.430
MJ.

283
00:13:53.530 --> 00:13:54.560
I just heard.

284
00:13:54.660 --> 00:13:56.700
- What can I do?
- Oh. Artie.

285
00:13:56.760 --> 00:13:59.070
- all we can do is pray.
- Who's that?

286
00:13:59.170 --> 00:14:01.800
Artie.
Gary's first handler.

287
00:14:08.610 --> 00:14:10.980
You better not have that
damn dog with you again.

288
00:14:11.710 --> 00:14:13.580
And you shouldn't
be taking strays home

289
00:14:13.680 --> 00:14:16.050
and you sure as hell shouldn't
have them on job with you!

290
00:14:16.150 --> 00:14:17.990
Copy that. boss.

291
00:14:18.120 --> 00:14:19.990
- Dog ain't here.
- I mean it. Franks.

292
00:14:20.120 --> 00:14:21.420
No more warnings.

293
00:14:21.490 --> 00:14:24.660
I got a possum
on 1826 River Drive.

294
00:14:24.790 --> 00:14:27.500
Go take care of it.
Out.

295
00:14:29.330 --> 00:14:30.470
What is wrong with you?

296
00:14:35.140 --> 00:14:36.970
You always bring a dog with you?

297
00:14:37.070 --> 00:14:38.640
You said you got
a possum. right?

298
00:14:38.740 --> 00:14:41.480
- Well. what's his name?
- Uh...

299
00:14:41.610 --> 00:14:42.810
dog.

300
00:14:42.910 --> 00:14:45.610
Well. I only caught
a glimpse of him. but

301
00:14:45.710 --> 00:14:47.650
I know a possum's eyes
when I see them.

302
00:14:47.750 --> 00:14:48.850
Been looting
my vegetable garden.

303
00:14:48.980 --> 00:14:50.720
What are you doing with that?

304
00:14:51.620 --> 00:14:52.960
I'll shake him loose for you.

305
00:14:53.660 --> 00:14:56.260
- Come on. get out of there.
- Hey. That ain't necessary.

306
00:14:56.320 --> 00:14:58.590
- Come on.
- Put the rake down.

307
00:14:58.690 --> 00:15:00.830
You're scaring my dog.

308
00:15:00.930 --> 00:15:03.370
Oh. oh. He's coming out.
He's coming out.

309
00:15:06.530 --> 00:15:07.670
Uh-oh.

310
00:15:07.770 --> 00:15:10.010
That ain't no possum.

311
00:15:10.110 --> 00:15:13.540
Who don't know the difference
between a possum and a skunk?

312
00:15:13.640 --> 00:15:15.540
This isn't the guy's fault.

313
00:15:15.640 --> 00:15:17.110
You shouldn't have had
the dog there.

314
00:15:17.210 --> 00:15:18.680
Glad I got fired.

315
00:15:18.780 --> 00:15:22.120
County don't care about animals.
they just want them out the way.

316
00:15:22.180 --> 00:15:23.720
Job was gonna make me mean.

317
00:15:23.820 --> 00:15:25.720
You could never be mean. Mike.

318
00:15:25.850 --> 00:15:27.560
Your heart's too big.

319
00:15:27.660 --> 00:15:29.760
- Ugh.
- You were right. though.

320
00:15:29.860 --> 00:15:32.530
Nobody gonna take this dog.

321
00:15:32.630 --> 00:15:34.530
Can't find him a home and...

322
00:15:34.630 --> 00:15:36.700
can't put him back
on the street.

323
00:15:37.500 --> 00:15:38.730
Please don't leave me.

324
00:15:38.870 --> 00:15:40.640
I'm not leaving.

325
00:15:40.740 --> 00:15:43.310
But I did call my Uncle Tango
for advice.

326
00:15:43.370 --> 00:15:45.810
And he told me
there's this guy Artie

327
00:15:45.910 --> 00:15:49.010
at this agency called NIS
who's starting a K-9 unit.

328
00:15:49.110 --> 00:15:50.250
Dog don't listen
to a damn thing.

329
00:15:50.350 --> 00:15:51.710
You think he's gonna be a cop?

330
00:15:51.810 --> 00:15:54.580
Tango says these K-9 dogs
are really expensive.

331
00:15:54.680 --> 00:15:57.590
and this agency has no money.

332
00:15:57.690 --> 00:15:59.620
He thinks they'll take him.

333
00:16:00.560 --> 00:16:02.820
What do you think. dog?

334
00:16:02.920 --> 00:16:05.260
Can you do it?

335
00:16:13.700 --> 00:16:16.240
Why is Randolf out in the hall

336
00:16:16.340 --> 00:16:17.710
doing push-ups?

337
00:16:17.810 --> 00:16:19.870
Exercising makes Randy happy.

338
00:16:19.970 --> 00:16:21.380
and when he's happy.
he says he's better

339
00:16:21.480 --> 00:16:23.050
at doing his Chatty Cathy thing.

340
00:16:23.110 --> 00:16:25.180
- Where's Gibbs?
- He's dropping the knife

341
00:16:25.250 --> 00:16:27.950
and all the other stuff
we found at forensics.

342
00:16:29.620 --> 00:16:31.220
Here comes Cathy.

343
00:16:31.290 --> 00:16:32.890
Hey. buddy.
Sorry to keep you waiting.

344
00:16:32.950 --> 00:16:34.760
But before we get into

345
00:16:34.860 --> 00:16:36.220
the nitty-gritty.
I just wanted to say

346
00:16:36.320 --> 00:16:38.060
we talked to some of your
friends at the encampment

347
00:16:38.130 --> 00:16:40.700
and. boy.
I heard a lot of great things.

348
00:16:41.460 --> 00:16:43.600
They said that you. uh.
look out for them.

349
00:16:43.730 --> 00:16:45.070
That you're the protector.

350
00:16:45.170 --> 00:16:46.770
We all need someone
looking out for us.

351
00:16:46.870 --> 00:16:49.970
I'm actually
in the process... ugh...

352
00:16:50.070 --> 00:16:51.770
of finding a godfather
for my son.

353
00:16:51.870 --> 00:16:53.880
You know. God forbid.
in case anything ever happens

354
00:16:53.940 --> 00:16:55.240
to me and the wife.

355
00:16:55.340 --> 00:16:57.480
No more push-ups
before interrogations.

356
00:16:57.580 --> 00:16:59.650
It's a dangerous profession.
so it's. uh. it's time.

357
00:16:59.750 --> 00:17:02.120
You know?
There's just so many choices.

358
00:17:02.220 --> 00:17:05.320
so I'm just not sure
who I'm gonna...

359
00:17:08.260 --> 00:17:09.790
Yeah. this isn't gonna work.

360
00:17:09.890 --> 00:17:11.430
I came in here

361
00:17:11.490 --> 00:17:14.330
with a plan to hit you with
my Chatty Cathy. but I just...

362
00:17:15.160 --> 00:17:16.330
I can't do it.

363
00:17:19.130 --> 00:17:20.970
You stabbed our dog. man.

364
00:17:21.770 --> 00:17:23.310
I'm so mad at you.

365
00:17:23.410 --> 00:17:25.670
He was mauling me.
It was self-defense.

366
00:17:25.810 --> 00:17:27.480
Probably not the best argument
since you committed robbery.

367
00:17:27.570 --> 00:17:30.080
And-and what else was it?
Oh. yeah. you murdered a guy.

368
00:17:30.150 --> 00:17:31.810
I didn't kill him.

369
00:17:31.910 --> 00:17:34.150
Listen. I broke in

370
00:17:34.250 --> 00:17:35.950
to grab some food
for me and my friends.

371
00:17:36.020 --> 00:17:37.850
and I saw him
lying there all bloody.

372
00:17:37.950 --> 00:17:40.020
All right? Next thing I know.
I-I heard sirens

373
00:17:40.120 --> 00:17:41.420
and there were cops everywhere.

374
00:17:41.490 --> 00:17:43.460
I freaked out.
I went to the woods to hide

375
00:17:43.560 --> 00:17:44.990
until things calmed down.

376
00:17:45.830 --> 00:17:47.500
But your dog found me.

377
00:17:49.530 --> 00:17:50.530
What'd I miss?

378
00:17:50.630 --> 00:17:53.000
He admitted to stabbing Gary

379
00:17:53.100 --> 00:17:55.670
but not killing Javier Martinez.

380
00:17:55.770 --> 00:17:57.040
Did Woody process the knife?

381
00:17:57.170 --> 00:17:58.510
Plum's prints are on it.

382
00:17:58.610 --> 00:18:00.410
but he needed more time
to test the blood.

383
00:18:00.510 --> 00:18:02.980
We found this silicone stuff

384
00:18:03.040 --> 00:18:04.580
inside Plum's backpack.

385
00:18:04.680 --> 00:18:07.050
He was using it
to waterproof all the tents.

386
00:18:07.150 --> 00:18:08.620
Is this the stuff
on Martinez's wrist?

387
00:18:08.720 --> 00:18:11.350
Woody thinks it could be.
but the Mass Spec is down.

388
00:18:11.450 --> 00:18:13.720
He's blaming Phil. saying
he forgot to recalibrate it.

389
00:18:13.860 --> 00:18:15.220
No. No.

390
00:18:15.960 --> 00:18:17.660
You know what I think?

391
00:18:17.760 --> 00:18:20.860
I think you
and whoever you were with

392
00:18:20.960 --> 00:18:22.530
broke in there
and killed Javier Martinez

393
00:18:22.630 --> 00:18:25.270
all for his watch
and a few bucks.

394
00:18:26.300 --> 00:18:27.570
We got the knife.

395
00:18:27.700 --> 00:18:29.540
Bloody boot prints.

396
00:18:30.910 --> 00:18:33.580
Come on man.
just admit to what you did.

397
00:18:33.680 --> 00:18:35.910
I think I want a lawyer now.

398
00:18:43.150 --> 00:18:45.520
Sorry. Herm. I got here
as soon as I could. How is he?

399
00:18:45.590 --> 00:18:47.290
He's still in surgery.

400
00:18:49.520 --> 00:18:50.760
Ma'am. need to use your phone.

401
00:18:50.860 --> 00:18:52.430
Look. man.
w-what are you doing here?

402
00:18:52.530 --> 00:18:54.060
Y-You should be out making sure
the dude that did this

403
00:18:54.160 --> 00:18:56.560
- is in prison.
- Caught the guy already.

404
00:18:56.660 --> 00:18:58.830
Homeless piece of...
Name's Adam Plum.

405
00:18:58.930 --> 00:19:00.600
- Rando's interrogating him now.
- Did they. uh. say

406
00:19:00.700 --> 00:19:03.140
he had a partner
you should be out looking for?

407
00:19:03.940 --> 00:19:05.610
Yeah. this is Franks.

408
00:19:07.740 --> 00:19:09.110
You sure?

409
00:19:10.950 --> 00:19:12.280
Okay.

410
00:19:14.750 --> 00:19:16.350
Listen. I don't need you here.

411
00:19:16.420 --> 00:19:17.520
That was Woody.

412
00:19:17.590 --> 00:19:19.150
The knife that stabbed Gary

413
00:19:19.250 --> 00:19:21.290
ain't the same one
that killed the grocery guy.

414
00:19:21.390 --> 00:19:22.760
There's only dog blood on it.

415
00:19:22.890 --> 00:19:24.190
Then you should get back
and find the murder weapon.

416
00:19:24.260 --> 00:19:25.460
Them bastards
probably ditched it.

417
00:19:26.360 --> 00:19:27.500
Don't matter none.

418
00:19:27.600 --> 00:19:28.860
Plum's the one
that did this to Gary.

419
00:19:28.930 --> 00:19:30.430
We'll catch his partner
another way.

420
00:19:31.600 --> 00:19:33.370
For Gary Callahan?

421
00:19:33.440 --> 00:19:35.100
- Yes.
- Yeah.

422
00:19:35.940 --> 00:19:37.410
I'm his handler.

423
00:19:37.470 --> 00:19:39.870
- Is he okay?
- The good news is he's stable.

424
00:19:39.940 --> 00:19:42.210
But the blade damaged
several nerves

425
00:19:42.310 --> 00:19:44.580
that control movements
in the hind legs.

426
00:19:44.650 --> 00:19:47.320
His recovery at this point
is unknown.

427
00:19:47.420 --> 00:19:50.320
but we have to be ready
for the possibility

428
00:19:50.420 --> 00:19:51.990
that he may not walk again.

429
00:19:52.090 --> 00:19:54.790
I have to go back in
to monitor him.

430
00:19:54.920 --> 00:19:58.860
I can answer any questions
when we discharge him later.

431
00:19:58.960 --> 00:20:01.000
Thank you. Doctor.

432
00:20:07.870 --> 00:20:09.000
This...

433
00:20:09.140 --> 00:20:11.170
all of this... is on you.

434
00:20:11.310 --> 00:20:13.010
- Excuse me?
- You should've had him on a leash.

435
00:20:13.110 --> 00:20:15.610
- What?
- He's not an attack dog.

436
00:20:15.710 --> 00:20:17.450
- I know that. You weren't there.
- That's right.

437
00:20:17.510 --> 00:20:19.010
You shouldn't have had him
out there without me.

438
00:20:19.110 --> 00:20:21.120
He-he's not a pet.
he's not your dog.

439
00:20:21.220 --> 00:20:22.450
I never said he was.

440
00:20:22.550 --> 00:20:23.920
You took him
to a JCPenney's photo shoot.

441
00:20:23.990 --> 00:20:25.820
- So what?
- He had training that day.

442
00:20:25.950 --> 00:20:27.590
He missed it
'cause your sorry ass

443
00:20:27.660 --> 00:20:29.690
wanted to take pictures
in a damn bolo tie.

444
00:20:29.820 --> 00:20:32.260
- Remember who you're talking to!
- I know who I'm talking to.

445
00:20:32.330 --> 00:20:35.500
You're the guy who breaks all
the rules to get what he wants.

446
00:20:35.600 --> 00:20:36.960
You wanted a pet?

447
00:20:37.060 --> 00:20:39.830
Well. congrats.
You got one.

448
00:20:39.970 --> 00:20:42.840
He'll never be able
to work again.

449
00:20:42.970 --> 00:20:44.610
That ain't what I wanted.

450
00:20:46.110 --> 00:20:48.040
That ain't never what I wanted.

451
00:20:48.910 --> 00:20:50.810
Yeah. you could've fooled me.

452
00:21:00.720 --> 00:21:02.590
Little help. please.

453
00:21:02.720 --> 00:21:04.230
Ladies. now. you know

454
00:21:04.360 --> 00:21:06.660
Herm has a small apartment.

455
00:21:06.730 --> 00:21:09.200
- Where is that thing gonna go?
- Sorry. MJ.

456
00:21:09.260 --> 00:21:11.100
there's a lot of letters
in "Gary Callahan."

457
00:21:11.230 --> 00:21:13.070
Big name. big banner.

458
00:21:13.200 --> 00:21:15.100
Could've just wrote "Gary."

459
00:21:15.200 --> 00:21:17.610
So. he's got
to retire now. right?

460
00:21:17.740 --> 00:21:19.170
Since he's immobile?

461
00:21:19.270 --> 00:21:21.040
Is he gonna go back
and live with his first owner?

462
00:21:21.110 --> 00:21:22.280
Mr. Callahan?

463
00:21:22.380 --> 00:21:24.380
I don't think
there is a Mr. Callahan.

464
00:21:24.450 --> 00:21:26.480
Franks gave him that name.
God knows why.

465
00:21:26.580 --> 00:21:29.580
He's the one who took Gary in
to begin with.

466
00:21:29.680 --> 00:21:31.290
Now that Gary's
out of commission.

467
00:21:31.420 --> 00:21:33.360
he'll go back to living
with Franks full-time.

468
00:21:33.420 --> 00:21:35.220
Aw...

469
00:21:35.320 --> 00:21:37.160
Wow. this is really sweet. guys.

470
00:21:37.260 --> 00:21:39.590
It's as much for Herm
as it is Gary.

471
00:21:39.690 --> 00:21:41.560
- He didn't sound good on the phone.
- Mm.

472
00:21:41.660 --> 00:21:43.930
I can't wait to give him and
Gary the world's biggest hugs.

473
00:21:44.030 --> 00:21:45.500
Uh. is the conference room
ready?

474
00:21:45.600 --> 00:21:47.200
- Uh. yeah. we're all set up.
- Ready for what?

475
00:21:47.300 --> 00:21:49.640
Uh. grocery store had
a fresh coat of paint on it.

476
00:21:49.770 --> 00:21:50.870
Turns out
a bunch of high school girls

477
00:21:50.940 --> 00:21:52.440
did it as a volunteer thing.

478
00:21:52.540 --> 00:21:54.580
So. you think one of them
stabbed the grocery store owner?

479
00:21:54.680 --> 00:21:56.410
No. but we do know
that Plum had a partner.

480
00:21:56.480 --> 00:21:58.050
And since these girls
were out painting.

481
00:21:58.110 --> 00:21:59.780
maybe one of them saw him
hanging around with somebody.

482
00:21:59.910 --> 00:22:01.150
Like. casing the joint.

483
00:22:01.250 --> 00:22:02.620
Exactamundo.

484
00:22:02.750 --> 00:22:04.320
Rando!

485
00:22:06.290 --> 00:22:07.490
Hey. um...

486
00:22:07.620 --> 00:22:10.090
JJ said he's really hoping
you pick him

487
00:22:10.190 --> 00:22:12.190
to be Junior's godfather.

488
00:22:12.290 --> 00:22:14.500
I think he'd be
a wonderful choice.

489
00:22:15.330 --> 00:22:17.160
Uh. noted. Yeah.

490
00:22:20.270 --> 00:22:22.170
What's the ETA
on them high school girls?

491
00:22:22.300 --> 00:22:24.140
Should be here any minute. boss.

492
00:22:28.480 --> 00:22:29.640
What are you doing?

493
00:22:29.740 --> 00:22:32.810
Times like this.
all I want to do is hug.

494
00:22:34.750 --> 00:22:36.650
All right.
That's enough.

495
00:22:37.490 --> 00:22:39.850
Adam Plum's been arrested
a dozen times.

496
00:22:39.990 --> 00:22:42.390
Four of those.
he had an accomplice.

497
00:22:42.490 --> 00:22:43.660
This guy.

498
00:22:43.760 --> 00:22:46.230
- Okay. he's probably our killer.
- Afraid not.

499
00:22:46.990 --> 00:22:48.960
He's been locked up in Metro
for six months.

500
00:22:49.030 --> 00:22:50.330
So. why would you put him
up on the board

501
00:22:50.430 --> 00:22:51.400
just to draw a big X
through his face?

502
00:22:51.500 --> 00:22:52.670
Because you're a visual learner.

503
00:22:52.770 --> 00:22:54.340
It's true. boss.

504
00:22:55.170 --> 00:22:57.140
Okay.
So. this yahoo gets locked up.

505
00:22:57.240 --> 00:22:58.540
Plum gets himself a new partner.

506
00:22:58.670 --> 00:23:00.480
probably one of the folks
he's living with

507
00:23:00.580 --> 00:23:01.640
at that encampment.

508
00:23:01.710 --> 00:23:03.010
I don't think so. boss.

509
00:23:03.110 --> 00:23:04.550
Just got off with Oceanside PD.

510
00:23:04.680 --> 00:23:06.950
They keep pretty good tabs
on everybody in there.

511
00:23:07.010 --> 00:23:08.420
said none are violent offenders.

512
00:23:08.520 --> 00:23:10.350
Plum's spent most his life
in juvies and jails.

513
00:23:10.450 --> 00:23:12.290
I'm sure he knows
plenty of violent offenders.

514
00:23:12.350 --> 00:23:13.860
Randy. the high school
girl painters

515
00:23:13.990 --> 00:23:15.720
- are here.
- Copy that.

516
00:23:15.860 --> 00:23:17.530
Gibbs. go with Rando.

517
00:23:20.600 --> 00:23:22.160
Plum was in Metro not long ago.

518
00:23:22.260 --> 00:23:23.600
I'll call the warden.

519
00:23:23.730 --> 00:23:25.070
find out who he was
hanging out with in there.

520
00:23:25.200 --> 00:23:27.270
Toss me that file. will you?

521
00:23:32.210 --> 00:23:33.610
He's still here. you know?

522
00:23:34.740 --> 00:23:37.910
I don't think most dogs
would have survived that.

523
00:23:43.850 --> 00:23:46.220
To start. I think it's so cool

524
00:23:46.320 --> 00:23:49.520
that. at your age.
you're volunteering.

525
00:23:49.590 --> 00:23:51.130
Giving back to the community.

526
00:23:51.230 --> 00:23:54.300
Huh? W-We're forced
to volunteer.

527
00:23:54.430 --> 00:23:56.800
- Why?
- To get into college.

528
00:23:58.470 --> 00:24:00.670
Yeah. that makes sense.

529
00:24:00.770 --> 00:24:02.400
He was so nice.

530
00:24:02.470 --> 00:24:04.440
The grocery store owner.

531
00:24:04.540 --> 00:24:06.570
When my mom told me
what happened. I felt bad

532
00:24:06.640 --> 00:24:08.440
I complained so much
about helping him.

533
00:24:08.580 --> 00:24:10.340
When you were painting.

534
00:24:10.440 --> 00:24:13.820
did you see this guy
hanging around at all?

535
00:24:15.050 --> 00:24:16.620
No.

536
00:24:16.750 --> 00:24:18.950
Is he the one who did it?

537
00:24:19.720 --> 00:24:21.990
No. No. no. I never saw him.

538
00:24:24.460 --> 00:24:26.160
You barely looked.

539
00:24:30.800 --> 00:24:33.000
Still never saw him.

540
00:24:36.470 --> 00:24:38.170
Yeah. I saw this guy.

541
00:24:38.270 --> 00:24:40.840
He was hanging around out back.

542
00:24:40.980 --> 00:24:42.240
Are you sure it was him?

543
00:24:42.310 --> 00:24:44.810
- Positive.
- Uh. was he-was he with anyone?

544
00:24:44.950 --> 00:24:47.720
Uh. yeah. actually.
Some other dude.

545
00:24:47.820 --> 00:24:49.950
Do you remember
what he looked like?

546
00:24:50.050 --> 00:24:52.490
He was really creeping me out.
staring right at me.

547
00:24:52.590 --> 00:24:54.120
He had a ponytail.

548
00:24:54.190 --> 00:24:57.090
brown hair and a goatee.

549
00:24:58.390 --> 00:24:59.990
I'm still waiting on my lawyer.

550
00:25:00.090 --> 00:25:02.160
You ain't got to talk.
I'm gonna.

551
00:25:02.960 --> 00:25:04.230
I've been up there
digging into your file.

552
00:25:04.330 --> 00:25:05.700
getting to know you.

553
00:25:05.800 --> 00:25:08.740
Read about all them foster homes
you came up in.

554
00:25:11.970 --> 00:25:13.340
I'm sorry to see that you got

555
00:25:13.470 --> 00:25:15.740
slapped around pretty good
in one of them.

556
00:25:17.880 --> 00:25:19.210
What is this?

557
00:25:19.310 --> 00:25:20.480
Memory lane?

558
00:25:20.580 --> 00:25:22.620
You needed a friend. huh?

559
00:25:22.680 --> 00:25:24.890
Someone to look out for you.

560
00:25:26.350 --> 00:25:27.760
And you found one.

561
00:25:29.720 --> 00:25:31.760
Says in your file
you and this Charlie fella

562
00:25:31.860 --> 00:25:34.630
was thick as thieves
in foster care.

563
00:25:35.360 --> 00:25:37.730
You know what's also
interesting about him?

564
00:25:38.500 --> 00:25:42.070
He's got a string
of armed robberies and assaults.

565
00:25:42.200 --> 00:25:44.370
What are you getting at?

566
00:25:45.840 --> 00:25:49.040
I know y'all did this together.

567
00:25:49.140 --> 00:25:51.310
and I know he did the stabbing.

568
00:25:51.380 --> 00:25:53.480
Charlie didn't have
anything to do with this.

569
00:25:53.580 --> 00:25:56.380
I got an eyewitness
that begs to differ.

570
00:25:56.480 --> 00:25:57.850
He wears his hair
in a ponytail now.

571
00:25:57.950 --> 00:25:59.420
trimmed his beard
down to a goatee. right?

572
00:25:59.520 --> 00:26:02.020
I have no idea.
I haven't seen him in months.

573
00:26:02.120 --> 00:26:03.960
Your witness is lying.

574
00:26:05.060 --> 00:26:07.630
Makes it their word
against mine. though. right?

575
00:26:08.660 --> 00:26:10.730
Yeah. I know how this goes.

576
00:26:11.830 --> 00:26:13.670
No one ever trusts
a guy like me.

577
00:26:14.540 --> 00:26:16.270
Know why?

578
00:26:17.610 --> 00:26:20.410
Because I'm a creep.
A weirdo.

579
00:26:21.380 --> 00:26:23.950
Like that song
they keep playing on the radio.

580
00:26:24.750 --> 00:26:26.280
Every time I hear it.

581
00:26:26.380 --> 00:26:30.080
I think they wrote that song
for me and everyone like me.

582
00:26:31.090 --> 00:26:34.490
You really gonna
fall on the spear for this guy?

583
00:26:36.020 --> 00:26:38.790
I could tell you the truth
till I'm blue in the face.

584
00:26:39.630 --> 00:26:40.700
Won't matter.

585
00:26:40.800 --> 00:26:42.630
Never does.

586
00:26:50.370 --> 00:26:52.140
Ain't no way he's gonna
give his buddy up.

587
00:26:52.240 --> 00:26:54.280
Tell me we got a lead
on where this prick is.

588
00:26:54.380 --> 00:26:57.440
Not yet. But we know
he's been writing bad checks.

589
00:26:57.540 --> 00:26:58.950
Woody and Phil
are gonna try to do

590
00:26:59.050 --> 00:27:00.580
their forensic accounting thing
to track him

591
00:27:00.650 --> 00:27:03.150
- while we comb the streets.
- You can ride with me.

592
00:27:05.620 --> 00:27:07.090
What?

593
00:27:08.490 --> 00:27:09.820
Gary's here.

594
00:27:20.740 --> 00:27:24.170
I sent Herm for a shower
and a sandwich.

595
00:27:24.940 --> 00:27:26.710
Looked like he needed it.

596
00:27:29.280 --> 00:27:30.780
That's how Herm rolled him in.

597
00:27:30.850 --> 00:27:33.650
I'd comment how ridiculous
Gary looked

598
00:27:33.750 --> 00:27:35.850
in that thing.
but it would be inappropriate.

599
00:27:35.980 --> 00:27:38.050
given the situation now.

600
00:27:39.190 --> 00:27:40.520
Look.

601
00:27:40.650 --> 00:27:43.360
I try to stay
out of others' affairs...

602
00:27:44.360 --> 00:27:45.930
but seems to me. uh.

603
00:27:45.990 --> 00:27:48.530
you and Herm
got some talking to do.

604
00:27:48.660 --> 00:27:50.260
What'd he tell you?

605
00:27:50.330 --> 00:27:51.830
Not much.

606
00:27:51.930 --> 00:27:54.040
I could see he was upset.

607
00:27:54.770 --> 00:27:56.540
Mentioned there were doings.

608
00:27:57.470 --> 00:27:58.970
If by "doings."
you mean he unloaded

609
00:27:59.070 --> 00:28:00.940
a bunch of crap on me
that wasn't true. then yeah.

610
00:28:01.010 --> 00:28:03.710
there were some
unforgivable doings.

611
00:28:08.520 --> 00:28:10.790
When he wakes up. uh.

612
00:28:10.890 --> 00:28:12.890
give him one of these treats.
will you?

613
00:28:13.020 --> 00:28:15.220
They're freshly baked.

614
00:28:37.010 --> 00:28:38.480
You're gonna kick back. relax

615
00:28:38.580 --> 00:28:41.250
and live the good life
with me now. okay?

616
00:28:42.020 --> 00:28:44.220
It'll be like you never left.

617
00:28:45.220 --> 00:28:47.860
He really likes it when
you scratch him behind his ears.

618
00:28:47.920 --> 00:28:49.590
- Especially the left one.
- All right. well.

619
00:28:49.720 --> 00:28:52.230
let me get in there. Let me
get in there. Ah. that's good.

620
00:28:52.360 --> 00:28:53.930
Yeah. that's good.

621
00:28:54.060 --> 00:28:56.400
You really think he's got
the makings of a K-9 cop?

622
00:28:56.500 --> 00:28:58.930
'Cause he don't listen too good.
and he destroys everything.

623
00:28:59.070 --> 00:29:01.870
Uh. no. he...
he's a German shepherd.

624
00:29:01.970 --> 00:29:03.340
They're meant for it.

625
00:29:03.440 --> 00:29:05.010
No. I think he's gonna love it.

626
00:29:05.070 --> 00:29:06.570
And he'll be living with you?

627
00:29:06.670 --> 00:29:08.780
Yeah. the wife
already okayed it.

628
00:29:10.440 --> 00:29:12.450
Where's he gonna sleep?

629
00:29:12.550 --> 00:29:14.550
I just went to the Pet Warehouse

630
00:29:14.620 --> 00:29:17.220
and I got him a bed.
the most expensive one they had.

631
00:29:17.280 --> 00:29:20.320
The gal that worked there.
she said it was the best.

632
00:29:26.030 --> 00:29:27.730
Did you hear that. buddy?

633
00:29:28.460 --> 00:29:30.730
You got a fancy bed now
and a real home.

634
00:29:34.370 --> 00:29:36.600
You don't need this one no more.

635
00:29:49.680 --> 00:29:51.690
He's a miracle dog.

636
00:29:54.990 --> 00:29:57.390
You take good care of him.
Agent Artie.

637
00:29:57.460 --> 00:29:58.630
I will.

638
00:29:58.760 --> 00:30:00.060
Okay.

639
00:30:00.860 --> 00:30:02.800
I'm gonna walk away now.

640
00:30:10.100 --> 00:30:11.810
Hey. uh. Mr. Franks.

641
00:30:11.910 --> 00:30:13.940
W-What's his name?

642
00:30:18.210 --> 00:30:20.210
His name's Gary.

643
00:30:24.850 --> 00:30:26.220
Gary Callahan.

644
00:30:28.490 --> 00:30:31.190
Special Agent Gary Callahan.

645
00:30:32.490 --> 00:30:34.160
I love you. buddy.

646
00:31:06.290 --> 00:31:08.100
Morning.

647
00:31:11.300 --> 00:31:12.930
- I didn't wake him. did I?
- No.

648
00:31:13.030 --> 00:31:16.270
All them pain pills and whatnot
got him zonked pretty good.

649
00:31:16.370 --> 00:31:18.210
Take the bus here?

650
00:31:18.970 --> 00:31:22.740
Gibbs and Randy dropped me off
on the way to Forensics.

651
00:31:22.810 --> 00:31:24.180
Hi.

652
00:31:25.680 --> 00:31:28.850
This Charlie Cline... he still
on the side of a milk carton?

653
00:31:28.950 --> 00:31:31.790
Yeah.
We checked every soup kitchen.

654
00:31:31.920 --> 00:31:33.790
shelter. homeless encampment
in the county.

655
00:31:33.920 --> 00:31:35.120
No one's seen him.

656
00:31:35.260 --> 00:31:36.960
- Forensics?
- Woody and Phil have been up

657
00:31:37.060 --> 00:31:38.830
all night trying
to track the bad checks

658
00:31:38.960 --> 00:31:40.830
Cline's been writing.

659
00:31:44.930 --> 00:31:46.700
What?

660
00:31:48.640 --> 00:31:50.570
Guy who stabbed Gary.

661
00:31:51.340 --> 00:31:54.080
Adam Plum. I've been up
all night reading about him.

662
00:31:55.110 --> 00:31:57.310
His background. his life.

663
00:31:59.410 --> 00:32:01.480
You find anything?

664
00:32:02.550 --> 00:32:04.450
All his cases
had one thing in common.

665
00:32:04.520 --> 00:32:06.890
He was always looking out
for someone else.

666
00:32:06.990 --> 00:32:08.490
I'm not surprised.

667
00:32:08.590 --> 00:32:10.020
Everyone living
in that encampment

668
00:32:10.160 --> 00:32:11.530
talked about him
like he's Mother Teresa.

669
00:32:11.660 --> 00:32:13.860
Said he was stealing
from that grocery

670
00:32:13.960 --> 00:32:15.430
so they had something to eat.

671
00:32:15.500 --> 00:32:18.700
Mother Teresa don't stab dogs.

672
00:32:19.870 --> 00:32:21.540
But last night.
when Gary was awake...

673
00:32:23.070 --> 00:32:25.510
he was looking at me like...

674
00:32:27.210 --> 00:32:28.540
you know.

675
00:32:29.340 --> 00:32:30.880
Like what?

676
00:32:30.980 --> 00:32:34.450
Like he looks when he's
telling me to be a better man.

677
00:32:34.520 --> 00:32:36.220
Wow. Mike.

678
00:32:36.350 --> 00:32:37.880
I didn't realize you and Gary

679
00:32:37.990 --> 00:32:39.720
talked about stuff like that.

680
00:32:40.520 --> 00:32:42.220
Not with words.

681
00:32:43.020 --> 00:32:44.560
You know.

682
00:32:46.860 --> 00:32:48.830
What else we got
on tracking down this yahoo?

683
00:32:48.930 --> 00:32:50.130
Woody's. uh...

684
00:32:50.230 --> 00:32:52.870
What'd you say Woody was doing?

685
00:32:53.700 --> 00:32:55.300
Ugh. You guys are early.

686
00:32:55.370 --> 00:32:57.900
I told you to come by
at 10:00 a.m.. okay?

687
00:32:58.040 --> 00:33:00.270
I'm still looking through
all these forged checks

688
00:33:00.370 --> 00:33:01.880
and bank statements.

689
00:33:01.980 --> 00:33:03.380
Yeah. we were hoping maybe
you were ahead of schedule.

690
00:33:03.480 --> 00:33:04.710
What's going on here?

691
00:33:05.550 --> 00:33:07.350
Phil thought it would inspire me
to have the man

692
00:33:07.410 --> 00:33:11.320
that I'm looking for
peering down at me all night.

693
00:33:11.420 --> 00:33:12.550
He was wrong.

694
00:33:12.650 --> 00:33:14.020
Hmm.

695
00:33:14.090 --> 00:33:16.220
- Where is Phil?
- Sleeping. in the back.

696
00:33:16.360 --> 00:33:17.320
Wrong.

697
00:33:17.390 --> 00:33:18.890
You thought I was sleeping.

698
00:33:18.990 --> 00:33:21.060
but I was up all night
working on this doggy wheelchair

699
00:33:21.160 --> 00:33:22.500
for Gary Callahan.

700
00:33:22.560 --> 00:33:24.270
Aw. It's got lightning bolts

701
00:33:24.400 --> 00:33:25.600
- and everything.
- Yeah.

702
00:33:25.700 --> 00:33:27.570
Great. now I'm the jerk.

703
00:33:27.700 --> 00:33:29.900
- Oh. hey. I. uh. I know you're looking for a godfather.
- Hey.

704
00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:32.410
Uh. I need to withdraw my name
from consideration.

705
00:33:32.540 --> 00:33:34.510
I'm godfather
to 19 kids already.

706
00:33:34.610 --> 00:33:36.510
and I just...
I can't handle another one.

707
00:33:36.610 --> 00:33:39.450
Dang.
The search continues.

708
00:33:39.550 --> 00:33:40.650
Thank you.

709
00:33:40.750 --> 00:33:43.150
Well. that's a kick
in the balls.

710
00:33:43.250 --> 00:33:44.490
That was the bank.

711
00:33:44.590 --> 00:33:45.890
Turns out this guy Charlie

712
00:33:45.950 --> 00:33:47.620
you guys had me
looking for all night...

713
00:33:47.750 --> 00:33:49.590
been forging checks
in Muncie. Indiana

714
00:33:49.690 --> 00:33:51.230
- for weeks.
- You sure?

715
00:33:51.330 --> 00:33:53.230
Yeah.
He's not your killer.

716
00:33:53.290 --> 00:33:55.360
And I've been up all night
for no reason.

717
00:33:55.430 --> 00:33:56.760
- I'm furious.
- Hmm.

718
00:33:56.900 --> 00:33:58.170
Sounds like I had
a far more productive night.

719
00:33:58.270 --> 00:34:00.400
I mean. doggy wheelchair.
obviously.

720
00:34:00.470 --> 00:34:02.100
but I also figured out
what the substance

721
00:34:02.240 --> 00:34:03.940
on your victim's wrist is.

722
00:34:04.040 --> 00:34:05.510
Oh. the Mass Spec
is working again?

723
00:34:05.610 --> 00:34:07.110
Yeah. Woody forgot
to recalibrate it.

724
00:34:07.210 --> 00:34:08.110
so I handled it.

725
00:34:08.210 --> 00:34:09.280
Not to belabor the point.

726
00:34:09.380 --> 00:34:10.710
but I had
a super productive night.

727
00:34:10.810 --> 00:34:12.610
The substance wasn't
the silicone grease

728
00:34:12.750 --> 00:34:14.450
used to weatherproof
the encampment tents.

729
00:34:14.580 --> 00:34:15.820
It's a glycerin-based gel

730
00:34:15.920 --> 00:34:17.820
I couldn't find
a precise match for.

731
00:34:17.950 --> 00:34:19.650
But when I put it
under the microscope.

732
00:34:19.790 --> 00:34:22.290
I saw what looked like
a tiny fleck of something

733
00:34:22.420 --> 00:34:24.190
I figured out was glitter.

734
00:34:24.290 --> 00:34:27.960
Turns out the substance
on your victim's wrist

735
00:34:28.060 --> 00:34:30.230
is the specific gel they use

736
00:34:30.300 --> 00:34:32.330
to fill those. uh.
colorful bracelets

737
00:34:32.470 --> 00:34:34.300
all the kids are wearing.

738
00:34:35.700 --> 00:34:37.840
Yeah. I saw this guy.

739
00:34:39.840 --> 00:34:41.210
Boss?

740
00:34:41.310 --> 00:34:43.640
Hey.
Warrant came through.

741
00:34:43.740 --> 00:34:45.580
We got Bridgette Donovan's
jacket.

742
00:34:45.650 --> 00:34:47.650
I don't know the names of
the high school girls. probie.

743
00:34:47.750 --> 00:34:49.020
Is she the one that lied to us?

744
00:34:49.150 --> 00:34:51.190
Yeah. Mike. the bracelet girl.

745
00:34:51.290 --> 00:34:52.620
You sure he's ready for this?

746
00:34:52.690 --> 00:34:54.490
Gimpy and stoned.
it don't matter.

747
00:34:54.620 --> 00:34:56.820
He's got the best sniffer
this side of the Mississippi.

748
00:34:56.920 --> 00:35:00.160
Killer's torn shirt
from the crime scene.

749
00:35:01.830 --> 00:35:04.330
- Get up in there. Gare.
- All right.

750
00:35:04.470 --> 00:35:06.030
And here's two random shirts

751
00:35:06.130 --> 00:35:08.030
I grabbed down
at the locker room.

752
00:35:08.140 --> 00:35:10.070
They'll act as our baseline.

753
00:35:11.670 --> 00:35:13.370
One.

754
00:35:18.480 --> 00:35:20.310
- Nothing.
- Okay.

755
00:35:20.380 --> 00:35:22.380
Moment of truth.

756
00:35:23.980 --> 00:35:26.220
Bracelet girl's jacket.

757
00:35:30.820 --> 00:35:32.560
Yeah.

758
00:35:32.660 --> 00:35:34.430
- Good boy.
- Nice.

759
00:35:34.530 --> 00:35:36.230
Good job. Gary.

760
00:35:36.360 --> 00:35:38.030
Good job. Gare bear.

761
00:35:40.170 --> 00:35:41.770
Girls got the idea
while they were painting

762
00:35:41.870 --> 00:35:44.240
Javier's grocery store
with their friends.

763
00:35:44.370 --> 00:35:46.170
They had everything.

764
00:35:46.240 --> 00:35:47.810
Rich folks.

765
00:35:47.910 --> 00:35:50.910
all the opportunities
in the world.

766
00:35:53.250 --> 00:35:56.720
But they said their lives
were mapped out by other people

767
00:35:56.820 --> 00:35:59.720
and wanted to feel the rush.

768
00:35:59.850 --> 00:36:01.150
So. they went back late.

769
00:36:01.220 --> 00:36:04.060
Black ski masks
and daddy's hunting knife.

770
00:36:04.160 --> 00:36:07.160
Said they wanted to steal
the old man's watch

771
00:36:07.260 --> 00:36:09.100
just to prove to themselves
that they could.

772
00:36:09.200 --> 00:36:10.730
But things got out of hand.

773
00:36:10.860 --> 00:36:12.170
He fought back.

774
00:36:12.270 --> 00:36:13.470
Next thing you know.
it's an all-out brawl.

775
00:36:13.570 --> 00:36:14.800
He lost.

776
00:36:14.900 --> 00:36:16.600
We only had the goods
on the bracelet girl.

777
00:36:16.740 --> 00:36:19.940
but that little rat sold her
pal out in about two seconds.

778
00:36:20.070 --> 00:36:21.240
You seeing this?

779
00:36:23.180 --> 00:36:24.580
It's Doug Westmont.

780
00:36:24.710 --> 00:36:26.880
Wilson and Barnes
have won the property battle

781
00:36:26.980 --> 00:36:28.750
and seized the land

782
00:36:28.850 --> 00:36:31.820
that belonged
to Abe Pruitt's community.

783
00:36:31.920 --> 00:36:34.590
That fool's on television
more than the president is.

784
00:36:34.690 --> 00:36:36.920
He's just doing his job.
But did you hear what he said?

785
00:36:37.020 --> 00:36:38.530
People on the compound
are being displaced.

786
00:36:38.630 --> 00:36:40.290
The hell are you
defending him for?

787
00:36:40.390 --> 00:36:42.030
You know who that is.
It's Abe Pruitt.

788
00:36:42.130 --> 00:36:44.200
- He's a bloodsucking lawyer.
- Boss. uh. sorry to interrupt.

789
00:36:44.300 --> 00:36:45.830
Nadia had a message for you.
She said to tell you

790
00:36:45.930 --> 00:36:48.600
she put the cassette you were
asking for on your desk.

791
00:36:48.700 --> 00:36:49.970
Why didn't she tell me herself?

792
00:36:50.100 --> 00:36:51.510
'Cause Wheeler's in here
and he scares her.

793
00:36:53.970 --> 00:36:55.980
Hey. boss. seeing as how
you're taking care

794
00:36:56.080 --> 00:36:58.410
of Gary Callahan so good
got me thinking.

795
00:36:58.510 --> 00:36:59.950
on a scale of one to ten.
what's your interest level

796
00:37:00.050 --> 00:37:01.320
in being Junior's godfather?

797
00:37:01.450 --> 00:37:03.350
- Zero.
- Copy that.

798
00:37:03.450 --> 00:37:05.150
Where you going?

799
00:37:05.250 --> 00:37:07.390
You didn't eat your sandwich.

800
00:37:07.450 --> 00:37:09.320
You can have it.
I ain't got an appetite.

801
00:37:09.420 --> 00:37:10.920
And. uh...

802
00:37:11.660 --> 00:37:13.990
Gary told me
to take care of something.

803
00:37:15.760 --> 00:37:17.500
Gary Callahan talks to you?

804
00:37:24.610 --> 00:37:25.770
You were right.

805
00:37:25.870 --> 00:37:28.140
It wouldn't have mattered
what you said.

806
00:37:28.240 --> 00:37:30.040
I wasn't gonna believe you.

807
00:37:30.140 --> 00:37:32.480
I wouldn't have
believed me. either.

808
00:37:36.480 --> 00:37:38.220
Pop it in. Danny.

809
00:37:43.820 --> 00:37:45.190
What are you doing. man?

810
00:37:45.290 --> 00:37:47.430
This song.

811
00:37:48.630 --> 00:37:50.200
This "creep" stuff.

812
00:37:50.330 --> 00:37:52.170
This ain't you. brother.

813
00:37:52.970 --> 00:37:55.000
No one ever gave you a chance.

814
00:37:55.100 --> 00:37:58.670
Deck was stacked against you.
just like that dog you stabbed.

815
00:38:05.950 --> 00:38:08.420
I helped him
and I'm gonna help you. too.

816
00:38:08.520 --> 00:38:11.220
You're gonna go do
this little stint of time.

817
00:38:11.320 --> 00:38:13.590
When you get out. I'm gonna
help you get on your feet.

818
00:38:19.090 --> 00:38:22.230
Thank you.

819
00:38:31.300 --> 00:38:33.710
Gary forgives you
for what you done to him.

820
00:38:33.840 --> 00:38:35.710
He told me to do the same.

821
00:38:37.980 --> 00:38:39.550
Hey. uh...

822
00:38:43.120 --> 00:38:44.590
I'm-I'm...

823
00:38:45.350 --> 00:38:47.450
I'm really sorry
I hurt your dog.

824
00:38:49.420 --> 00:38:52.960
Takes a stand-up man
to admit when they screwed up.

825
00:39:01.230 --> 00:39:02.570
Herm.

826
00:39:03.300 --> 00:39:05.610
Getting ready for the ceremony?

827
00:39:06.710 --> 00:39:08.110
You need something?

828
00:39:09.210 --> 00:39:10.880
You know. I...

829
00:39:12.010 --> 00:39:14.150
I never wanted to give Gary up.

830
00:39:16.080 --> 00:39:19.590
Seemed coming here
was the best thing for him.

831
00:39:20.390 --> 00:39:24.120
Yeah. Artie told me he was
a maniac in the beginning.

832
00:39:25.030 --> 00:39:26.290
Yeah. he really was.

833
00:39:26.430 --> 00:39:28.430
He needed structure.

834
00:39:28.530 --> 00:39:30.230
But I missed him.

835
00:39:31.060 --> 00:39:33.030
Part of the reason
why I started working here.

836
00:39:33.100 --> 00:39:34.770
To spend more time with him.

837
00:39:35.600 --> 00:39:37.970
Tried to have my cake
and eat it too. you know?

838
00:39:38.940 --> 00:39:40.410
Yeah.

839
00:39:41.270 --> 00:39:42.740
And I noticed you started
eating way more cake

840
00:39:42.840 --> 00:39:44.280
after Tish left.

841
00:39:45.510 --> 00:39:46.950
You know. I never
should have had him out there

842
00:39:47.080 --> 00:39:48.980
without a leash.

843
00:39:52.920 --> 00:39:55.490
I never should've have had him
out there without you.

844
00:39:58.630 --> 00:40:00.560
I appreciate that. Franks.

845
00:40:00.630 --> 00:40:02.960
I know how much you love him.

846
00:40:09.770 --> 00:40:11.670
I know how much
you love him. too.

847
00:40:13.310 --> 00:40:14.740
One more thing.

848
00:40:14.840 --> 00:40:16.740
God forbid anything ever happens
to Rando and Junie.

849
00:40:16.810 --> 00:40:19.180
I told Rando you'd be happy
to raise his kid.

850
00:40:20.050 --> 00:40:21.680
You earned it. pal.

851
00:40:22.450 --> 00:40:26.050
Gary Callahan made an impact
on all of us.

852
00:40:26.150 --> 00:40:28.660
Detail. attention.

853
00:40:28.760 --> 00:40:32.090
We were all better
for having known him.

854
00:40:32.190 --> 00:40:34.500
He was one hell
of a special agent.

855
00:40:34.600 --> 00:40:36.460
We've gathered here today
to recognize

856
00:40:36.530 --> 00:40:39.030
the courage and valor
of one of our own.

857
00:40:39.170 --> 00:40:42.000
K-9 Agent Gary Callahan.

858
00:40:45.470 --> 00:40:47.210
We are here today to welcome

859
00:40:47.310 --> 00:40:49.380
the newest member of our team.

860
00:40:49.510 --> 00:40:53.080
Congratulations
to our inaugural K-9.

861
00:40:53.180 --> 00:40:55.550
Agent Gary Callahan.

862
00:41:03.420 --> 00:41:05.790
He was your dog. right?

863
00:41:05.860 --> 00:41:07.230
Sure was.

864
00:41:08.030 --> 00:41:10.130
Uh. Special Agent Cliff Wheeler.

865
00:41:10.200 --> 00:41:13.970
Artie told me you got fired
for rescuing him.

866
00:41:14.070 --> 00:41:17.240
He also mentioned you were
a vet. A Marine. right?

867
00:41:18.870 --> 00:41:21.010
Yeah. So?

868
00:41:21.810 --> 00:41:23.910
You know. we hire humans. too.

869
00:41:26.480 --> 00:41:28.250
I don't got the makings
of a cop.

870
00:41:28.350 --> 00:41:30.550
That's what I thought. too.

871
00:41:30.680 --> 00:41:33.820
when I was a seventh grade
biology teacher.

872
00:41:35.560 --> 00:41:37.390
Give it some thought.

873
00:41:42.530 --> 00:41:44.870
Above and beyond
the line of duty.

874
00:41:44.930 --> 00:41:47.630
So. without further ado...

875
00:41:53.610 --> 00:41:55.680
Maybe it was just grit.

876
00:41:55.740 --> 00:41:58.080
or hell.

877
00:41:58.210 --> 00:41:59.950
maybe it was a miracle.

878
00:42:00.080 --> 00:42:01.720
But in that moment.

879
00:42:01.780 --> 00:42:05.090
Gary Callahan stood up...

880
00:42:06.050 --> 00:42:09.590
and took his first steps
for the second time.

881
00:42:09.690 --> 00:42:12.630
He's walking!
He did it again!

882
00:42:16.930 --> 00:42:19.130
How about that?

883
00:42:20.770 --> 00:42:22.240
He was born the runt
of his litter.

884
00:42:22.300 --> 00:42:24.770
He was a miracle dog.

885
00:42:25.770 --> 00:42:28.910
And he wasn't done
being an agent yet.

886
00:42:28.980 --> 00:42:31.410
Franks and Herm
worked out the custody

887
00:42:31.480 --> 00:42:33.310
so Franks only had him
on weekends.

888
00:42:36.250 --> 00:42:38.220
And on work days. well...

889
00:42:40.950 --> 00:42:43.090
he still had the best sniffer

890
00:42:43.160 --> 00:42:45.160
this side of the Mississippi.
